# Files Docker should not ship into the build context. Smaller
# context means faster `COPY .` and a smaller image; tracked here
# alongside `.gitignore` since the two have overlapping intent but
# Docker uses its own ignore file.

# Version control: huge tree of small objects, never useful inside
# the image.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Local CI / IDE caches.
.clangd
.ccls-cache/
.cache/
compile_commands.json

# Editor swap files.
*.swp
*~

# Extension build artefacts.
src/*.o
src/*.bc
*.so
sql/provsql--*.sql
sql/provsql.sql
test/schedule
provsql.control
tdkc
provsql_migrate_mmap
test.log
test/results/
test/regression.diffs
test/regression.out

# Documentation, website source, and branding assets are only used
# by `make docs` / `make website` to build the hosted provsql.org
# pages; the image never reads them. Note: the top-level
# `doc/*.md` files (notably `doc/provsql.md`, the README) ARE
# referenced by `make install` via PGXS's DOCS variable, so we
# keep `doc/` itself and only exclude the heavy subtrees.
doc/source/
doc/doxygen-c/
doc/doxygen-sql/
website/
branding/

# Studio dev artefacts.
studio/.venv/
studio/.pytest_cache/
studio/dist/
studio/build/
studio/provsql_studio.egg-info/
**/__pycache__/

# Claude / scratch files.
**/.claude/
TODO.md
